						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated the <hi rend="bold">4th year of</hi> the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalla, [Du]rmati,</hi> the other details being effaced. <hi rend="bold">Siṅgi-[Nāyaka]</hi> and other Nāyakas are stated to have contributed a portion of the toll-revenue for the service of the god Rāmēśvara in addition to the grant of a village. Paleographically, the record may be assigned to the reign of Jagadēkamalla II. In that case it should be read before No. 238.</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
